Brazilian Finance Minister  Guido
Mantega  said International Monetary Fund head Dominique Strauss-
Kahn has the right to defend himself against charges and that
all G20 countries should be consulted before any decision on a
replacement should he leave the post, according to an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
